Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of metamorphic testing to test a bioinformatics software tool for processing biomedical text. This involves aspects of software engineering (cs.SE) such as testing and quality assurance, as well as natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques used in the tool. Additionally, the paper touches on issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and potentially cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) if the tool is used in a medical setting.
